Terry Fator is a "real entertainer."  He is an excellent ventriloquist and his showmanship is superb.

Good fun.  There are alot of little changes to the show itself from the other Terry Fator DVD Live From Vegas.  This show is also tighter than the Live From Vegas show but that could be considered a good or bad thing.  There is a fun in being loose as the Live From Vegas show was.  On the flipside, this show has less mistakes.  Yet, It has that "Just another show" vibe instead of being truly special.  Like today, they decided to just record this particular show and put it on DVD, ho-hum.  The first one Live From Vegas felt important.  Also, there are some puppet changes.

There aren't many giant changes and some material is recycled.  The extra DVD Special Features are new and solid.  If your a Terry Fator nut, you'll appreciate this DVD as a whole.  It'll be different enough to be worth owning.  It's a high quality production and looks/sounds great.  It's also great if you never owned the Vegas disc.  But if you did and your not a Terry Fator nut.  Consider it first.  My family watching it was split 50/50.  Some loving it wholeheartedly and others saying "the other one was better".  I think the big problem is simply, if you've seen it once.  It's not as special seeing it again.  Unless your a super fan, that makes all the difference.

The Amazon ad says this DVD was released in May 2014 so I was expecting newer material.  Unfortunately this DVD was made in 2012 so the material is at least 4 years old.  His newer material is NOT on this DVD.

Terry Fator has some new puppets and routines in Las Vegas and has improved some of his old puppets and material as well. You get a large variety of music and jokes here and their are plenty of bonuses in the special feature including a short cartoon. If you saw the first one "Live in Las Vegas" you need to get this one next.

The best part of the video was the song about the little boy and the horses, which he said was a true story.  Also, the song on behalf of the military that he wrote.  Other than that, we were highly disappointed that his known puppet characters have changed in appearance.  Edgar Bergan, Paul Winchell and Sherri Lewis never changed their puppets.  If you are going to change puppets, at least change the name.  It was a disappointing video.

If you never saw "from Las Vegas" then this portion of the review is for you.  Terry Fator is a ventriloquist who also sings for his puppets.  Just think "Jeff Dunham with songs" and you'll get the basic idea.  Terry is a great entertainer and I enjoy watching his DVDs.  I do believe this is his second DVD.  He sings and makes jokes with his puppets.

If you did see "from Las Vegas" then this portion of the review is for you.  There is good and there is bad.  The good part is, this is a new show, a new DVD.  The bad part is, there are some repeats from the first DVD.  I never saw Terry live, only on the DVDs and I must say, if he is still doing some of the same acts 3 years later.....what is up with him?  Get some new material, Terry!  Example (SPOILER ALERT!) is the Elvis puppet.  Same material as in the first DVD.  Just bumped into him (Elvis impersonator) downstairs in the lobby.  Hello!  You bumped into him on your first DVD back in 2009.  This one is from 2012 and you just bumped into him again?  Come on!  Anyway, it is a good DVD to own/watch.  Just know that there is a few repeats from the first DVD in there, but there is also more new material too.

There is a reason that I cannot give this concert 5 stars. I truly enjoy Terry Fator, but if you already own his first Live in Concert like I do then you will not need to buy this one. Yes, you guessed it the show is almost the exact same. Now if you don't already own a Terry Fator concert then you are in for a musical treat, mixed with comedy entertainment. Terry is very talented and he brings music to ventriloquism like Jeff Dunham brings comedy to ventriloquism. Terry brings 8 puppets to life and he will sing a few songs without them. This is a great live concert and Terry has been headlining his own Las Vegas show for four straight years. Terry is a singing impersonator that will truly keep the family entertained.

Had just seen Terry Fator in person for the first time @ The Fox in Riverside & he was AWESOME! His live show was more autobiographical, less puppets but no less amazing. This disc had more of his supreme talent without his co-stars than his earlier DVD but not as much as his live show. There are some tearjerker moments when he sings two songs he wrote himself. Some of his co-stars have had a little work done, Julius in particular.  A couple of bits are works in progress & it's strange for him to have imperfect moments but it proves he's human after all. Not 100% child friendly but it is a Vegas show, after all.

I was very "unimpressed" with this new video.  It's basically an updated version of his first DVD and he even uses some of the same jokes and taglines.  It's more singing with the puppets and he introduces a few new ones, but they are less than "exciting".  I feel like I wasted my money on this video - the first one was 10 times funnier.  He still pulls someone out of the audience and dresses them up like a woman (1st video it was Cher, this video it's Dolly Parton).  The lines are same and it's nothing new. Overall, I say save your money and wait until he really has something new and refreshing to offer his audience.  He talks about how he didn't have any control over the first video and everyone was trying to "run" his career, but he took back control this time, and the result is a video that is worse than his first.  Perhaps he's a little too narcissistic to realize this first video with other producers who know what people want put out a much better video than this one will ever be! Don't get me wrong, I think he is extremely talented, I just thought I'd be getting a video with new "characters" and new material.  That wasn't the case.  I wish I hadn't wasted the money on this "repeat".
